A 3d printed case is now available for the Arduino shutter tester.
All parts are shown on one plate, but it is best to print the parts seperately.

It is designed to use 13mm diameter buttons, a DIN socket (the socket could be negated and the wire just runn through the hole)
and a USB-C to USB-c chassis mount extension cable. 
Details of these parts can be found in the parts list document.

3d print files are also available for sensor and Laser enclosures.
These can be found in the ESP32 V4 folder.
